    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Stackable Washer & Dryer Repair", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/services/stackable-washer-dryer-repair/" }
  ]
}
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How much does stackable washer and dryer repair cost?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Our diagnostic fee is $89, applied toward the repair once you approve the work. Most stackable unit repairs run between $130 and $320. A door latch, thermal fuse, drain pump, or drum belt replacement is toward the lower end. Control board replacement on premium brands like Miele or Bosch runs higher. We provide a written estimate before any work begins."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Which areas of Southern California do you cover for stackable washer-dryer repair?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Same-day across Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties, West Hollywood and Silver Lake apartment closets, Newport Beach and Anaheim condo stacks, Thousand Oaks and Westlake Village townhomes, Long Beach high-rises, Rancho Cucamonga and Riverside ADUs and condos. Eight service territories total. LG WashTower, Samsung FlexWash, Bosch, Miele, Electrolux, Blomberg compact 24\" units. BHGS #A49573."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can you repair a stackable washer and dryer that's in a tight laundry closet?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. This is the most common setup we work with across SoCal apartments and condos. Many repairs on stacked front-load units can be completed from the front without pulling the units out. When the unit does need to come out, for a rear bearing replacement, for example, we know how to safely move a stacked pair in a tight space without damaging walls, flooring, or the units themselves."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My front-load washer smells like mildew, what causes that?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Mold and mildew growth on the door boot gasket (the rubber seal around the door opening) is extremely common in Southern California front-load washers, especially units installed in closed laundry closets without ventilation. SoCal's mild, humid coastal climate combined with a sealed closet creates ideal conditions for mold. The fix involves deep cleaning the gasket and treating for mold, and in advanced cases, gasket replacement. Leaving the door slightly ajar after each cycle, and the closet door open when not in use, prevents recurrence."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "My dryer takes forever to dry, is it broken?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Check the dryer vent first. A clogged or kinked vent duct is the single most common cause of long dry times, the dryer heats normally but can't exhaust moisture. In stacked units installed in closets, the vent duct is often short and kinked behind the stack, restricting airflow significantly. If the vent is clear and the dryer still runs long, the heating element, thermal fuse, or thermistor needs diagnosis."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Do you repair Bosch, Miele, and other European-brand stackable units?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Bosch, Miele, Electrolux, Blomberg, and ASKO stackable units are a significant part of what we service across SoCal's condo and apartment market. These brands have different diagnostic approaches than LG and Samsung, Bosch and Miele use error code systems that require brand-specific knowledge to interpret correctly. We carry OEM parts for Bosch specifically and source Miele parts from authorized distributors."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is a ventless or heat pump dryer and how is it different to repair?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "A ventless heat pump dryer doesn't require an external vent duct, it removes moisture by condensing it and collecting it in a reservoir. Common in new SoCal condos and apartments where installing a vent duct isn't possible, and increasingly common in ADU conversions across all five counties. Heat pump dryers have different failure modes than vented dryers: the heat pump compressor, evaporator coils, and condenser can fail independently. They don't use a traditional heating element, so 'not heating' on a heat pump dryer requires a completely different diagnostic approach than a vented unit."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "When does it make sense to repair vs replace a stackable washer-dryer?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Under 6 years old: repair almost always wins. 6–10 years on a premium brand (Bosch, Miele, LG WashTower, Samsung FlexWash) with a single component failure: repair, these units are built to last 12–15 years. 10+ years with drum-bearing failure or multiple component failures simultaneously: we'll quote both repair and replacement and tell you directly which makes more financial sense. New stackable pairs run $1,400–$2,500 (mid-range) to $3,500–$5,000+ (premium European compact + WashTower), plus install, and stacked install in tight closets has its own labor cost. We give the honest math."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does the 90-day warranty cover on stackable unit repairs?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Every repair we complete carries a 90-day warranty on both parts and labor. If the same issue returns within that window, we come back at no charge. That's in writing before we leave."
      }
    }
  ]
})} />

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  .hero { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 80px 24px 64px; text-align: center; }
  .hero-eyebrow { display: inline-block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 5px 14px; border-radius: 3px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
  .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(1.9rem, 4vw, 2.8rem); font-weight: 800; line-height: 1.15; margin: 0 0 20px; max-width: 820px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }
  .hero-sub { font-size: 1.1rem; color: #ccc; max-width: 620px; margin: 0 auto 32px; line-height: 1.6; }
  .cta-row { display: flex; gap: 14px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 16px 34px; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; }
  .btn-secondary { background: transparent; color: #fff; padding: 16px 34px; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none; border: 2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.35); }
  .hero-rating { margin-top: 28px; color: #aaa; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .hero-rating strong { color: #fff; }
  .stars { color: #f5b800; margin-right: 6px; }
  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); padding: 18px 24px; }
  .trust-inner { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px 32px; }
  .trust-item { color: #fff; font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .section { padding: 64px 24px; }
  .section-gray { background: var(--gray); }
  .section-black { background: var(--black); color: #fff; }
  .container { max-width: 1100px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .section-number { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 10px; }
  h2.section-title { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem); font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 16px; line-height: 1.2; }
  .section-black h2.section-title { color: #fff; }
  .lead { font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.75; color: var(--text); max-width: 720px; }
  .section-black .lead { color: #ccc; }
  .intro-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 320px; gap: 48px; align-items: start; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .intro-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .intro-body p { margin: 0 0 18px; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text); }
  .tip-box { background: #fff8e7; border: 1px solid #f0d070; border-radius: 8px; padding: 18px 20px; margin-top: 24px; }
  .tip-box .tip-label { font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: #a07000; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .tip-box p { font-size: 0.95rem; color: #5a4000; margin: 0; line-height: 1.65; }
  .sticky-cta { position: sticky; top: 24px; background: var(--black); border-radius: 10px; padding: 28px 24px; color: #fff; text-align: center; }
  .sticky-cta .cta-label { font-size: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: #aaa; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .sticky-cta .cta-phone { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 800; color: #fff; text-decoration: none; display: block; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .sticky-cta .btn-cta { display: block; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px; border-radius: 5px; font-weight: 700; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 10px; }
  .sticky-cta .cta-sub { font-size: 0.82rem; color: #888; }
