  .repair-card h3 { font-size: 0.98rem; font-weight: 700; color: #fff; margin: 0 0 10px; line-height: 1.3; }
  .repair-card p { font-size: 0.87rem; color: #888; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .repair-card .repair-detail { font-size: 0.78rem; color: #555; border-top: 1px solid #1e1e1e; padding-top: 10px; }
  /* Pricing */
  .pricing-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 18px; margin-top: 32px; }
  .price-card { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 22px 18px; text-align: center; }
  .price-card .price-label { font-size: 0.8rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .price-card .price-amount { font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .price-card .price-desc { font-size: 0.84rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.5; }
  .price-note { margin-top: 18px; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
  .faq-list { margin-top: 36px; }
  .faq-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 20px 0; }
  .faq-item:first-child { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .faq-item h3 { font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); margin: 0 0 10px; }
  .faq-item p { font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }
  .nearby-links { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 10px; margin-top: 24px; }
  .nearby-links a { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 4px; padding: 8px 16px; font-size: 0.87rem; color: var(--text); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; }
  .nearby-links a:hover { border-color: var(--red); color: var(--red); }
  .bottom-cta { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 64px 24px; text-align: center; }
  .bottom-cta h2 { font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 2.2rem); font-weight: 800; margin: 0 0 16px; }
  .bottom-cta p { color: #aaa; margin: 0 0 32px; font-size: 1.05rem; }
</style>

<!-- HERO + TRUST BAR (unified ServiceHero) -->
<ServiceHero
  title="Stackable Washer & Dryer Repair Across Southern California"
  subtitle="Same-day across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino & Riverside counties. Laundry closet, in-unit, or combo unit, our technicians work in tight spaces and know the front-load brands that power SoCal apartments, condos, and ADUs. BHGS #A49573."
  heroImageTitle="Stackable Washer & Dryer Repair"
/>

<!-- INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="intro-grid">
      <div class="intro-body">
        <p class="section-number">01, About This Service</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Stacked units in SoCal apartments have a specific set of problems, and a specific access challenge.</h2>

        <p>Half of Southern California lives in apartments, condos, ADUs, and smaller homes with a laundry closet instead of a laundry room, LA's apartment density is well-known, but Long Beach high-rises, Anaheim and Irvine OC condos, Thousand Oaks townhomes, and the IE's expanding ADU stock all share the same laundry-closet reality. The stacked washer-dryer pair in that 30-inch opening is often the only laundry option in the unit, when it goes down, it's urgent. The access challenge is real: most of the space around the units is occupied by the wall, the closet door frame, or the stacking bracket. Many repairs can be done from the front without moving the pair. When the unit does need to come out, we know how to move it without damaging the surrounding walls, flooring, or the units themselves.</p>

        <p>Front-load washers, the only type that stacks, have their own specific failure patterns in SoCal's climate. The door boot gasket (the rubber seal around the door) accumulates mold in closed closets without ventilation, producing the characteristic mildew smell that drives homeowners to call. SoCal's mild, humid coastal climate (LA Westside, OC coastal, Ventura coastal corridor) makes this worse than in drier inland markets. The fix is cleaning and preventive habits, not always a new gasket. We tell you which it is before billing for parts.</p>

        <p>On the dryer side, the most common "not drying well" call is a blocked vent duct, often kinked or compressed behind the stack in a tight closet. We check the vent before diagnosing a heating element failure. The second category growing rapidly in SoCal's new construction and ADU conversions: ventless heat pump dryers (Bosch, Miele, LG), which have different technology and completely different failure modes than vented units. Same-day service across all five counties, BHGS #A49573.</p>

        <div class="tip-box">
          <div class="tip-label">🌀 Check Dryer Vent First</div>
          <p>If your dryer runs but clothes take two cycles to dry, the vent duct is the first suspect. Pull the dryer away from the wall slightly (or have someone check behind the stack) and look for a kinked or compressed duct. A vent blocked to 30% capacity makes any dryer perform poorly regardless of whether the heating element is working. We clear the vent before diagnosing further.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="sticky-cta">
        <div class="cta-label">Same Day Stackable Repair</div>
        <a href={phoneHref} class="cta-phone">{phone}</a>
        <a href={phoneHref} class="btn-cta">Call Now, We Pick Up</a>
