<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">09, Frequently Asked Questions</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Stackable washer and dryer repair, what people ask us</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How much does stackable washer and dryer repair cost?</h3>
        <p>Our diagnostic fee is $89, applied toward the repair. Most repairs run between $130 and $320. A door latch, thermal fuse, drain pump, or drum belt is toward the lower end. Control board replacement on Miele or Bosch runs higher. Written estimate before any work begins.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Which areas of Southern California do you cover for stackable washer-dryer repair?</h3>
        <p>Same-day across <strong>Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties</strong>, West Hollywood and Silver Lake apartment closets, Newport Beach and Anaheim condo stacks, Thousand Oaks and Westlake Village townhomes, Long Beach high-rises, Rancho Cucamonga and Riverside ADUs and condos. Eight service territories total. LG WashTower, Samsung FlexWash, Bosch, Miele, Electrolux, Blomberg compact 24" units. BHGS #A49573.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can you repair a stackable unit in a tight laundry closet?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Most front-load repairs are done from the front without moving the units. When rear access is needed, we know how to safely move a stacked pair in a tight space without damaging walls or flooring.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My front-load washer smells like mildew, what causes that?</h3>
        <p>Mold on the door boot gasket is extremely common in SoCal laundry closets without ventilation. SoCal's mild, humid coastal climate combined with a sealed closet creates ideal mold conditions. The fix is cleaning the gasket and keeping the door ajar after each cycle. In advanced cases, gasket replacement is needed.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>My dryer takes forever to dry, is it broken?</h3>
        <p>Check the vent duct first. A kinked or blocked duct behind the stack is the single most common cause in SoCal laundry closets. If the vent is clear, the heating element, thermal fuse, or thermistor needs diagnosis. On heat pump dryers, a different diagnostic path applies entirely.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do you repair Bosch, Miele, and other European stackable units?</h3>
        <p>Yes. European compact (24") units from Bosch, Miele, Electrolux, and Blomberg are a significant part of what we service across SoCal. We carry OEM parts for Bosch and source Miele parts from authorized distributors. Heat pump dryer repair on these brands requires brand-specific knowledge, we have it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is a ventless heat pump dryer and how is it different to repair?</h3>
        <p>A heat pump dryer removes moisture by condensing it, no external vent duct required. Common in new SoCal condos and ADU conversions across all five counties. Different failure modes than vented dryers: heat pump compressor, evaporator coils, condenser. "Not heating" on a heat pump dryer requires a completely different diagnostic approach than a vented unit.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>When does it make sense to repair vs replace a stackable washer-dryer?</h3>
        <p>Under 6 years old: repair almost always wins. 6–10 years on a premium brand (Bosch, Miele, LG WashTower, Samsung FlexWash) with a single component failure: repair, these units are built to last 12–15 years. 10+ years with drum-bearing failure or multiple component failures simultaneously: we'll quote both repair and replacement and tell you directly which makes more financial sense. New stackable pairs run $1,400–$2,500 (mid-range) to $3,500–$5,000+ (premium European compact + WashTower), plus install, and stacked install in tight closets has its own labor cost. We give the honest math.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What does the 90-day warranty cover?</h3>
        <p>Every repair carries a 90-day warranty on both parts and labor. If the same issue returns within that window, we come back at no charge. That's in writing before we leave.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

